ENTRY       EC 3.4.24.28                Enzyme
NAME        bacillolysin;
            Bacillus metalloendopeptidase;
            Bacillus subtilis neutral proteinase;
            anilozyme P 10;
            Bacillus metalloproteinase;
            Bacillus neutral proteinase;
            megateriopeptidase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on peptide bonds (peptidases);
            Metalloendopeptidases
REACTION    Similar, but not identical, to that of thermolysin
COMMENT     Variants of this enzyme have been found in species of Bacillus including B. subtilis [1,6], B. amyloliquefaciens [5], B. megaterium (megateriopeptidase, [2]), B. mesentericus [10], B. cereus [3,8,9] and B. stearothermophilus [7]. In peptidase family M4 (thermolysin family). Formerly included in EC 3.4.24.4
HISTORY     EC 3.4.24.28 created 1972 as EC 3.4.24.4, part transferred 1992 to EC 3.4.24.28
